snippet.textDisplay:
You guys should do the ACURA TL specifucally one from the 3rd Gen window which are TLs dated 2004 to 2008.

Theres soooo much you could do with that car. I have a 3rd Gen TL (2004) and have done some minor mods on it.. nothing too spectacular, but still fun. This car is legendary in so many respects, for starters being one of the first "luxury sport" car models who delivered the "wedge shape" body style that is so popular and prominent in this specific class today... YEAH! THE TL IS ALMOST SINGLE HANDEDLY RESPONSIBLE FOR MAKING IT THE STANDARD LOOK, YA DINGUS!

Maybe if you did some reading up instead of playing around with your toy cars you'd learn something.

Wait,... I didn't mean that last part.

Anyway, the TL is the perfect candidate for a future season of Hi/Low. There are so many aftermarket and official parts you can add to beef it up and get 700hp out of the 3.2L v6 vTech engine... EVEN with my car having almost 200k miles on it... and the best part is... I bought my TL from the Acura dealership as a trade in... it had ONE pervious owner, an old wobbly guy (and his wobbly wife), and u paid only $5k. cash baby!!!

So yeah... do a future season, if not this next one, on the AMAZING IN EVERY SENSE OF THE WORD, 3RD GEN (04-08) ACURA TL...!!!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
You guys killed it with this series. Great idea, well executed. We all learned together and laughed at your pain.

Suspension - Mid Car (A name brand aftermarket, but perhaps not as much as High Car)
Wheels & Tires - Mid Car (Flow form rims with no-name tires with good specifications)
Brakes - Low Car (I ain't racing)
Interior - No car (Mid car seats, no cage)
Rear Dif - High Car or factory LSD
Paint - No car (touch up, paint less dent removal and a detail)
Turbo - Mid Car (Basic bold ons with a tune)

snippet.textDisplay: Do an E30 325i, but no forced induction, just engine tuning.  Focus more on more performance and daily driveability.  Let's not focus on the aesthetics, that's all gonna come down to everyone's personal taste, time, and budget.  But this first season is a great because you guys did a good overview of what everyone wants to do a car in general.  Real car guys care more about mechanical reliability and performance first, everything else is second.  If not an E30 than a miata, afterall, I'm sure you guys have to work in a budget, if money isn't an issue than go with an E46 M3 😉
